6quot%3B%20Trudeau%20told%20the%20Canadian%20Broadcasting%20Corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20US%20indictment%20appears%20to%20have%20convinced%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20adopt%20a%20more%20sober%20tone.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20understanding%20that%20maybe%2C%20maybe%20just%20churning%20out%20attacks%20against%20Canada%20isn't%20going%20to%20make%20this%20problem%20go%20away.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20in%20a%20situation%20of%20having%20a%20fight%20with%20India%20right%20now%20over%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20be%20working%20on%20that%20trade%20deal.%20We%20want%20to%20be%20advancing%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20is%20foundational%20for%20Canada%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20people's%20rights%2C%20for%20people's%20safety%2C%20and%20for%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20And%20that's%20what%20we're%20going%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%20The%20ties%20between%20India%20and%20Canada%20came%20under%20severe%20strain%20following%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20on%20September%2018%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bpotential%26quot%3B%20involvement%20of%20Indian%20agents%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistani%20separatist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20on%20June%2018%20in%20British%20Columbia.%20India%20had%20designated%20Nijjar%20as%20a%20terrorist%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20rejected%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20as%20%26quot%3Babsurd%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bmotivated%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20the%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20charged%20that%20one%20Nikhil%20Gupta%20was%20working%20with%20an%20Indian%20government%20employee%20in%20the%20foiled%20plot%20to%20kill%20a%20Sikh%20separatist%2C%20who%20holds%20dual%20citizenship%20of%20the%20US%20and%20Canada.%20Though%20the%20separatist%20Sikh%20leader%20was%20not%20named%2C%20media%20reports%20identified%20him%20as%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice%2C%20an%20