p%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%2C%20the%20nine%20bail%20pleas%20were%20clubbed%20together%20by%20Justice%20Mridul%E2%80%99s%20bench%20as%20they%20arose%20from%20the%20same%20FIR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20all%20the%20petitions%20were%20almost%20always%20listed%20on%20the%20same%20dates%20for%20a%20hearing.%20However%2C%20listing%20of%20a%20case%20does%20not%20guarantee%20that%20a%20judge%20would%20hear%20the%20case%20that%20day.%20A%20case%20may%20not%20be%20taken%20up%20either%20because%20of%20lack%20of%20time%2C%20an%20adjournment%20request%20or%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscirf.gov%2Freligious-prisoners-conscience%2Fforb-victims-database%2Fmeeran-haider%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHaider%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20PhD%20research%20scholar%20at%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%20and%20a%20political%20activist%2C%20filed%20his%20bail%20plea%20in%20May%202022.%20Since%20then%2C%20his%20case%20has%20been%20listed%2060%20times.%20However%2C%20arguments%20took%20place%20only%20on%20four%20dates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20proceedings%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20issuance%20of%20notice%2C%20calling%20for%20counter%20affidavits%20or%20other%20procedural%20work%20%E2%80%93%20happened%20on%20five%20other%20dates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2060%20days%20his%20case%20was%20listed%2C%20there%20were%20a%20total%20of%20nine%20productive%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty%20times%2C%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20orders%20noted%20that%20the%20special%20bench%20%E2%80%9Cdid%20not%20assemble%E2%80%9D%2C%20seven%20times%20due%20to%20one%20judge%20on%20the%20bench%20being%20on%20leave%20or%20unavailable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Arjun%20Dewan%2C%20counsel%20for%20one%20of%20the%20other%20accused%2C%20Athar%2C%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EArticle%2014%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20special%20bench%20may%20have%20found%20it%20difficult%20to%20assemble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Mridul%20and%20Justice%20Bhatnagar%20were%20both%20heading%20separate%20benches%20and%20had%20to%20especially%20sit%20together%20to%20form%20this%20special%20bench.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20which%20could%20have%20been%20a%20hassle%20sometimes%20because%20each%20had%20their%20own%20roster%20and%20heavy%20workload%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dewan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CA%20regular%20bench%20sits%20every%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhile%20a%20special%20bench%20sits%20once%20a%20week%20usually.%20So%20a%20regular%20bench%20could%20have%20heard%20the%20cases%20more%20expeditiously.%20Hence%20you%20see%20so%20many%20times%20the%20court%20orders%20noting%20that%20the%20bench%20did%20not%20assemble.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%2022%20times%2C%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20orders%20simply%20note%20that%20the%20case%20was%20ordered%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Crenotified%E2%80%9D%20on%20another%20specific%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FvKnmkzO8ShA%3Fsi%3DAA0XVUDydibxVm5g%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20means%20that%20the%20bench%20did%20assemble%20but%20was%20either%20hearing%20the%20case%20of%20another%20co-accused%20in%20that%20batch%20of%20nine%20cases%20or%20did%20not%20have%20time%20to%20hear%20any%20of%20the%20nine%20cases%20despite%20assembling%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dewan%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EArticle%2014%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaider%E2%80%99s%20plea%20was%20adjourned%20nine%20times%20%E2%80%93%20five%20on%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20asking%20and%20the%20rest%20on%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20asking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20eight%20cases%20proceeded%20in%20an%20identical%20manner.%20The%20bench%20listed%20Saleem%E2%80%99s%20case%2058%20times%2C%20Rehman%E2%80%99s%20case%2057%20times%2C%20Fatima%E2%80%99s%20case%2054%20times%2C%20Saifi%E2%80%99s%20and%20Imam%E2%80%99s%20cases%2046%20times%20each%2C%20Ahmed%E2%80%99s%20case%2041%20times%2C%20Malik%E2%80%99s%20case%2036%20times%20and%20Athar%E2%80%99s%20case%2034%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20January%20and%20March%20this%20year%2C%20the%20bench%20concluded%20hearing%20arguments%20from%20both%20sides%20and%20reserved%20its%20judgements%20in%20the%20bail%20pleas%20of%20Haider%2C%20Malik%2C%20Saleem%2C%20Rehman%2C%20Saifi%20and%20Fatima%20but%20did%20not%20deliver%20a%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20the%20remaining%20three%20accused%20%E2%80%93%20Ahmed%2C%20Athar%2C%20and%20Imam%20%E2%80%93%20the%20court%20continued%20to%20list%20their%20cases.%20While%20the%20court%20heard%20arguments%20by%20Ahmed%E2%80%99s%20and%20Athar%E2%80%99s%20lawyers%2C%20arguments%20in%20Imam%E2%80%99s%20plea%20never%20made%20it%20to%20the%20argument%20stage%20despite%20being%20listed%20over%2046%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20scandal%20that%20a%20bail%20application%20should%20be%20adjourned%20anywhere%20between%2034%20to%2060%20times%20and%20even%20after%20concluding%20hearings%20not%20to%20deliver%20judgement%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Chandru%20told%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Article%2014%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStandstill%20after%20July%202023%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%202%2C%202023%2C%20a%20case%20related%20to%20three%20other%20co-accused%20in%20the%20conspiracy%20case%20came%20up%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20The%20Delhi%20police%20had%20challenged%20a%20June%2015%2C%202021%20Delhi%20high%20court%20order%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fdelhi-high-court-grants-bail-to-devangana-kalita-natasha-narwal-and-asif-iqbal-tanha-in-delhi-riots-case-175719%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egranting%20bail%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20three%20of%20the%2020%20co-accused%20in%20the%20same%20conspiracy%20case%20%E2%80%93%20activists%20Devangana%20Kalita%2C%20Natasha%20Narwal%20and%20Asif%20Iqbal%20Tanha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-dismisses-delhi-polices-challenge-against-bail-granted-to-3-student-leaders-in-delhi-riots-conspiracy-case-227733%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edismissed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20police%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20and%20indicated%20that%20the%20other%20co-accused%20in%20the%20FIR%20could%20argue%20for%20bail%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20parity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20enable%20the%20nine%20accused%20before%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20to%20ask%20the%20judges%20to%20look%20into%20whether%20their%20role%20in%20the%20case%20is%20largely%20similar%20to%20Kalita%2C%20Narwal%20and%20Tanha%2C%20and%20if%20so%2C%20grant%20bail%20on%20parity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20in%20May%20and%20July%2C%20three%20of%20the%20six%20whose%20bail%20orders%20were%20reserved%20by%20Justice%20Mridul%E2%80%99s%20bench%20%E2%80%93%20Haider%2C%20Fatima%20and%20Saifi%20%E2%80%93%20filed%20an%20application%20seeking%20bail%20on%20parity.%20This%20resulted%20in%20their%20cases%20being%20reopened.%20The%20bench%20would%20again%20have%20to%20hear%20both%20sides%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20parity%20and%20then%20deliver%20its%20judgements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fumar-khalid-the-historian-his-continued-imprisonment-is-a-loss-to-the-academic-world%5C%22%3EUmar%20Khalid%2C%20the%20Historian%3A%20His%20Continued%20Imprisonment%20Is%20a%20Loss%20to%20the%20Academic%20World%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20July%205%2C%202023%2C%20the%20day%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20collegium%20recommended%20Justice%20Mridul%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20to%20the%20Manipur%20high%20court%2C%20the%20bench%20did%20not%20hold%20extensive%20hearings%20in%20any%20of%20the%20pending%20cases%2C%20despite%20listing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20bench%20could%20have%20been%20hesitant%20to%20go%20forward%20with%20the%20matter%20perhaps%20because%20the%20collegium%20had%20recommended%20Justice%20Mridul%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20in%20July%2C%20and%20a%20little%20while%20later%2C%20Justice%20Bhatnagar%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20in%20August%2C%E2%80%9D%20Harsh%20Bora%2C%20Fatima%E2%80%99s%20advocate%2C%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EArticle%2014%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20this%20is%20not%20what%20people%20expect%20from%20the%20courts%2C%20especially%20those%20like%20the%20accused%20who%20have%20already%20spent%20many%20years%20in%20custody.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandru%2C%20the%20former%20Madras%20high%20court%20judge%2C%20said%20whether%20a%20particular%20judge%20is%20under%20transfer%20or%20not%20should%20not%20impact%20the%20hearing%20of%20bail%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20senior%20judge%20%5BJustice%20Mridul%5D%20was%20recommended%20for%20transfer%20and%20if%20he%20still%20was%20hopeful%20of%20his%20transfer%2C%20he%20should%20have%20released%20the%20case%20to%20the%20chief%20justice%20to%20constitute%20some%20other%20bench%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20should%20not%20be%20any%20relationship%20between%20his%20transfer%20move%20and%20his%20continued%20keeping%20of%20the%20cases%20under%20his%20list%20without%20orders.%20You%20cannot%20satisfy%20both%20sides%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Chandru.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20constitutional%20oath%20taken%20by%20the%20judge%20must%20guide%20him%20to%20decide%20the%20matter%20without%20fear%20or%20favour%20and%20to%20the%20best%20of%20his%20abilities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20verdict%20in%20three%20cases%20waiting%20for%20decisions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Saleem%2C%20Malik%2C%20and%20Rehman%20choosing%20not%20to%20apply%20for%20bail%20on%20grounds%20of%20%E2%80%98parity%E2%80%99%20(that%20three%20co-accused%20in%20the%20same%20conspiracy%20case%2C%20Devangana%20Kalita%2C%20Natasha%20Narwal%20and%20Asif%20Iqbal%20Tanha%2C%20had%20been%20granted%20bail%20by%20the%20high%20court%20and%20the%20bail%20order%20had%20been%20upheld%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court)%2C%20the%20bench%20failed%20to%20deliver%20a%20judgement%20even%20in%20their%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGautam%20Khazanchi%2C%20Saleem%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%2C%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EArticle%2014%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20everyone%20hoped%20the%20bench%20would%20at%20least%20pass%20its%20verdicts%20on%20those%20accused%20individuals%E2%80%99%20bail%20pleas%20who%20did%20not%20file%20parity%20applications%2C%20which%20would%20have%20required%20fresh%20arguments%20to%20be%20heard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20the%20matters%20were%20reserved%20by%20March%2C%20one%20did%20hope%20that%20at%20least%20those%20matters%20which%20were%20not%20re-opened%20could%20be%20decided%20at%20the%20earliest%20considering%20they%20were%20bail%20applications%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khazanchi%20said.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Justice%20Mridul%E2%80%99s%20bench%20failed%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDewan%2C%20the%20lawyer%20for%20co-accused%20Athar%2C%20said%20the%20bench%20may%20have%20decided%20to%20wait%20until%20all%20nine%20bail%20pleas%20were%20heard%20and%20reserved%20for%20judgement.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%20this%20does%20not%20usually%20happen%20in%20bail%20matters.%20In%20my%20experience%2C%20bail%20pleas%20are%20decided%20within%2030-40%20days%20max.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandru%20said%20that%20a%20bail%20application%20has%20to%20%E2%80%9Cstand%20on%20its%20own%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20question%20of%20similar%20applications%20of%20bail%20by%20different%20persons%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20arise%20unless%20the%20matter%20relates%20to%20some%20legal%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CBail%20applications%20are%20heard%20on%20their%20own%20merits%20and%20there%20are%20cases%20where%20one%20gets%20bail%20and%20others%20in%20the%20same%20case%20are%20denied%20due%20to%20several%20circumstances%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20too%20has%20repeatedly%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fpdf_upload-378832.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemphasised%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20%E2%80%9Cdelay%20in%20the%20pronouncement%20of%20judgement%20is%20opposed%20to%20the%20principle%20of%20law%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20prescribed%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F448-umesh-rai-gora-rai-v-union-of-india-15-may-2023-475712.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix-month%20limit%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20pronouncing%20a%20verdict%20in%20a%20reserved%20matter%2C%20failing%20which%20the%20case%20must%20go%20before%20a%20fresh%20bench%20for%20a%20rehearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%2C%20as%20recently%20as%20July%202022%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fadvisable-that-high-court-delivers-judgement-soon-after-conclusion-of-arguments-supreme-court-203773%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvised%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0high%20courts%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdeliver%20the%20judgement%20at%20the%20earliest%20after%20the%20arguments%20are%20concluded%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEffects%20of%20Centre%20vs%20collegium%20power%20tussle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20of%20these%20nine%20cases%20also%20reveals%20the%20tangible%20repercussions%20of%20the%20ongoing%20power%20struggle%20between%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20collegium%20concerning%20the%20tr