the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.davp.nic.in%2Fwritereaddata%2FFinal_Print_Media_Advt_Policy_Revision_dated_23072020.pdf%5C%22%3EPrint%20Media%20Advertisement%20Policy%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20said%20policy%2C%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Outreach%20and%20Communication%2C%20a%20nodal%20agency%20set%20up%20in%202017%2C%20empanels%20newspapers%20in%20which%20advertisements%20will%20be%20placed.%20A%20newspaper%20should%20have%20a%20minimum%20circulation%20of%202%2C000%20copies%20per%20day%20to%20be%20considered%20eligible%20for%20empanelment.%20The%20policy%20mandates%20that%2080%25%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20newspaper%20advertisements%20be%20reserved%20for%20Indian%20language%20dailies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20details%20of%20expenditure%20incurred%20by%20CBC%2C%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%2C%20on%20awareness%2Fpublicity%20campaigns%20about%20schemes%20and%20programmes%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India%20through%20print%20media%20from%202019-20%20to%202023-24%20(till%2012%20December%202023)%20is%20Rs%20967.46%20crore%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Thakur%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fgovt-spent-rs-96746-crore-on-advertisements-in-print-media-from-2019-20-to-2023-24-2817557%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20news%20agency%20PTI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20data%2C%20there%20were%201%2C19%2C995%20periodicals%2C%20including%20newspapers%2C%20registered%20with%20the%20Registrar%20of%20Newspapers%20for%20India%20(RNI)%20as%20of%20March%2031%2C%202019.%20The%20number%20subsequently%20rose%20to%201%2C43%2C423%20in%202020%2C%201%2C44%2C520%20in%202021%2C%201%2C46%2C045%20in%202022%2C%20and%201%2C48%2C363%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUttar%20Pradesh%20tops%20the%20list%20with%2021%2C660%20periodicals%20registered%20with%20the%20government%2C%20followed%20by%20Maharashtra%20with%2020%2C448%20periodicals%2C%20and