%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20has%20reclassified%20India%E2%80%99s%20exchange%20rate%20regime%20to%20%E2%80%9Cstabilised%20arrangement%E2%80%9D%20from%20%E2%80%9Cfloating%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20period%20from%20December%202022%20to%20October%202023.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20has%20told%20the%20IMF%20that%20the%20objective%20of%20frequent%20interventions%20in%20the%20forex%20market%20is%20to%20curb%20excessive%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20has%20also%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Finterventions-in-forex-market-to-curb-excessive-volatility-rbi-to-imf-123122000384_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dismissed%20the%20Fund%E2%80%99s%20rationale%20for%20reclassifying%20India%E2%80%99s%20exchange%20rate%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20executive%20director%20at%20IMF%2C%20K.V.%20Subramanian%20and%20senior%20advisors%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20Hansda%20and%20Anand%20Singh%2C%20said%20the%20classification%20is%20%E2%80%9Cincorrect%20and%20inconsistent%20with%20reality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20in%20the%20past%2C%20exchange%20rate%20flexibility%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20first%20line%20of%20defence%20in%20absorbing%20external%20shocks%2C%20with%20interventions%20limited%20to%20addressing%20disorderly%20market%20conditions%2C%20%E2%80%9D%20they%20said%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20has%20always%20claimed%20that%20its%20interventions%20in%20the%20interbank%20market%20which%20determines%20the%20exchange%20rate%20of%20the%20rupee%20is%20to%20curb%20excessive%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20now%20claimed%20that%20this%20methodology%20follows%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbackward-looking%20statistical%20approach%20that%20relies%20on%20past%20exchange%20rate%20movement%20and%20historical%20data.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20reclassification%20happened%20after%20an%20Article%20IV%20review%20of%20Indian%20policies.%20A%20report%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Fimf-reclassifies-indias-exchange-rate-regime-to-stabilised-arrangement-due-to-rbis-forex-interventions-11702962330433.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20notes%20that%20this%20consultation%20report%20reviews%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20current%20and%20medium%20term%20economic%20policies%20and%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20in%20the%20foreign%20exchange%20market%2C%20where%20the%20Indian%20rupee%20moved%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20narrow%20range%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20US%20dollar%2C%20the%20movement%20suggested%20that%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cintervention%20likely%20exceeded%20levels%20necessary%20to%20address%20disorderly%20market%20conditions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20reported%20that%20IMF%20has%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20exchange%20interventions%20have%20been%20used%20to%20avoid%20excessive%20volatility%20not%20warranted%20by%20fundamentals.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703073891000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fimf-indian-currency-rbi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22RBI's%20'intervention'%20in%20the%20foreign%20exchange%20market%20likely%20exceeded%20levels%20necessary%20to%20address%20disorderly%20market%20conditions%2C%20the%20IMF%20has%20held.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fimf-indian-currency-rbi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22If%20Congress%20Really%20Wants%20to%20Take%20on%20the%20BJP%2C%20Merely%20an%20Electoral%20Battle%20Won't%20Help%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06200522%2FF80eu2gWkAATe66.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20comprehensive%20victories%20registered%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20in%20the%20recent%20assembly%20elections%20of%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20well-wishers%20of%20the%20Congress%20have%20shown%20surprising%20optimism%20in%20their%20interpretation%20of%20the%20results.%20They%20say%20given%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Congress%20has%20retained%20much%20of%20its%20vote%20shares%20in%20these%20states%2C%20it%20still%20has%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20challenge%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20BJP%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20optimism%2C%20however%2C%20ignores%20the%20current%20predicament%20of%20Indian%20politics%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20challenge%20before%20the%20country%20is%20not%20merely%20electoral.%20It%20is%20a%20more%20serious%20socio-political%20challenge%2C%20and%20merely%20thinking%20of%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20an%20electoral%20solution%20without%20a%20simultaneous%20battle%20for%20the%20soul%20of%20this%20civilisation%20can%20be%20a%20misleading%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20question%20that%20the%20opposition%20forces%20must%20face%20sooner%20or%20later%20is%20whether%20they%20have%20the%20political%20and%20ideological%20strength%20to%20stop%20the%20divisions%20in%20the%20country%20and%20halt%20the%20multiplication%20of%20Hindutva%20votes%20at%20the%20grassroots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2-300x141.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27145721%2F404088963_1118521242975440_6389008391481424915_n-2-1024x480.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686558%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22563%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20group%20of%20women%20hold%20a%20poster%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20at%20an%20election%20rally%20in%20Rajasthan.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FNarendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuslims%20compensate%20for%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20loss%20of%20Hindu%20vote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20closer%20analysis%20of%20the%20assembly%20elections%20indicates%20that%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20where%20Scheduled%20Caste%20and%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20together%20make%20up%20for%20around%2065%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20Congress%20has%20lost%204%25%20and%206%25%20of%20its%20votes%20among%20these%20communities%20respectively.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20not%20only%20retained%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20SCs%20at%2033%25%2C%20but%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20OBCs%20has%20risen%20by%207%25%20from%2048%25%20to%2055%25.%20It%20has%20also%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs)%20by%209%25%20from%2030%25%20to%2039%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20among%20STs%20has%20also%20increased%20by%2011%25%20as%20compared%20to%202018%2C%20its%20highest%20increase%20of%20votes%20is%20among%20the%20Muslims.%20In%202018%2C%20only%2052%25%20of%20Muslims%20voted%20for%20Congress%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lokniti.org%2Fstate-election-studies%5C%22%3ECSDS-Lokniti%20Post%20Poll%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20this%20time%20around%2085%25%20of%20Muslims%20voted%20for%20it.%20A%20phenomenal%20increase%20of%20around%2033%25%20of%20Muslim%20votes%20is%20the%20single%20most%20reason%20behind%20the%20Congress%20holding%20on%20to%2040.40%25%20votes%20in%20spite%20of%20its%20loss%20of%20votes%20in%20its%20other%20social%20bases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muslim%20population%20of%20the%20MP%20is%20around%206.5%25%20and%20Congress%20might%20have%20reached%20its%20peak%20share%20among%20the%20Muslim%20community.%20Among%20many%20other%20things%2C%20one%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20behind%20the%20shift%20of%20OBCs%20and%20Adivasis%20towards%20BJP%20is%20the%20vicious%20Hindutva%20campaign%20by%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20and%20its%20organs%20consistently%20throughout%20the%20year%20without%20any%20political%20challenge.%20This%20will%20be%20amplified%20during%20the%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20resulting%20in%20further%20polarisation%20of%20Hindu%20OBCs%20and%20others.%20The%20INDIA%20bloc%20or%20the%20Congress%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20grassroots%20ideological%20or%20organisational%20counters%20to%20this%20challenge.%20Nor%20do%20they%20seem%20to%20have%20a%20vision%20of%20cultivating%20the%20same%20to%20provide%20an%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Congress%20obtained%20a%20vote%20share%20of%2043.04%25%20in%202018%2C%20and%20in%202023%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20its%20humiliating%20defeat%2C%20has%20retained%2042.23%25%20of%20the%20vote%20share.%20Thus%2C%20an%20argument%20is%20being%20made%20that%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20social%20base%20is%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20continues%20to%20have%20a%20good%20social%20base%20among%20the%20SCs%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20which%20has%20been%20reflected%20in%20the%20increase%20of%20SC%20votes%20by%206%25%20to%2048%25%20when%20compared%20to%2042%25%20in%202013%20as%20reflected%20in%20the%20CSDS%20analysis.%20But%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20STs%2C%20who%20constitute%2032%25%20of%20the%20state%20population%2C%20has%20decreased%20by%205%25%2C%20from%2047%20to%2042%25%2C%20and%20among%20OBC%20a%20further%20decrease%20of%203%25%2C%20from%2042%20to%2039%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthree-things-bjps-definitive-victory-in-the-assembly-elections-tells-us%5C%22%3EThree%20Things%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Definitive%20Victory%20in%20the%20Assembly%20Elections%20Tells%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decline%20in%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20among%20Hindus%20in%20the%20state%20is%20majorly%20compensated%20by%2C%20again%2C%20a%20phenomenal%20increase%20of%20Muslim%20votes%20by%2012%25%20(41%25%20to%2053%25).%20Unlike%20MP%2C%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20base%20among%20Muslims%20five-fold%2C%20from%20a%20mere%205%25%20to%2027%25.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20SCs%20of%20the%20state%20by%2014%25%20%C2%A0(25%25%20to%2039%25)%2C%20among%20the%20STs%20by%2021%25%20(25%25%20to%2046%25)%2C%20and%20among%20OBC%20by%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20honour%20of%2040%25%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20is%20majorly%20due%20to%20the%20arithmetic%20increase%20of%20votes%20by%20Muslims.%20Unlike%20MP%2C%20it%20is%20not%20saturated%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20but%20BJP%20itself%20has%20become%20a%20strong%20contender%20for%20Muslim%20votes%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Rajasthan%2C%20Congress%20polled%2039.53%25%20votes%2C%20hardly%201.11%25%20less%20than%20in%202018.%20The%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20by%20more%20than%202%25%20to%2041.69%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20what%20the%20CSDS%20survey%20informs%20us%20is%20that%20though%20the%20Congress%20has%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20by%209%25%20(39%25%20to%2048%25)%20among%20SCs%2C%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20STs%20has%20decreased%20by%206%25%20(41%20to%2035%25)%2C%20and%20among%20OBCs%20a%20decrease%20by%203%25.%20(36%20to%2033%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20its%20vote%20share%20could%20sustain%20its%202018%20figure%2C%20majorly%20because%20the%20Muslim%20vote%20share%20increased%20by%20an%20astounding%2028%25%20(62%25%20in%202018%20to%2090%25%20in%202023).%20The%20emergence%20of%20an%20independent%20Adivasi%20party%20has%20cut%20into%20the%20ST%20vote%20share%20of%20both%20BJP%20and%20Congress.%20But%20the%20BJP%20almost%20retained%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20SCs%20at%2033%25%20and%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20among%20the%20OBC%20by%205%25%2C%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20loss%20of%203%25%20vote%20share%20of%20OBC%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20phenomenal%20increase%20of%20Muslim%20votes%20for%20the%20Congress%20by%2012%25-31%25%20in%20the%20three%20states%20could%20compensate%20for%20its%20loss%20of%20votes%20among%20its%20traditional%20Hindu%20vote%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20survey%20also%20suggests%20that%20among%20the%20Hindus%2C%20especially%20SC%2C%20ST%2C%20and%20OBCs%2C%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20has%20either%20stagnated%20or%20sharply%20decreased.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20increased%20its%20Hindu%20vote%20share%20by%2016%20to%2034%25%20by%20encroaching%20upon%20the%20Congress%20social%20base%20of%20the%20SCs%2C%20STS%2C%20and%20OBCs.%20It%20is%20also%20reflected%20in%20the%20depleting%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20smaller%20parties%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20much%20to%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeing%20a%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20political%20replica%20won%E2%80%99t%20help%20Congress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20polarisation%20is%20ominous%20for%20the%202024%20elections.%20Even%20among%20the%20rural-urban%2C%20male-female%2C%20and%20other%20class%20categories%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20made%20significant%20inroads%2C%20with%20its%20twin%20agenda%20of%20communal%20polarisation%20and%20last-minute%20personalised%20welfare%20dole-outs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20it%20is%20already%20obvious%20that%20BJP-RSS%20is%20pitching%20on%20issues%20like%20national%20security%2C%20Ram%20Mandir%2C%20pride%20of%20Hindu%20Rashtra%2C%20and%20such%20mythical%20and%20emotive%20agendas%20to%20which%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%E2%80%99s%20counters%20are%20either%20collusive%20or%20complementary%20instead%20of%20confronting%20with%20alternate%20vision%20and%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electoral%20data%20of%20the%20recent%20assembly%20elections%20has%20many%20political%20and%20ideological%20lessons.%20It%20would%20be%20self-deception%20to%20take%20comfort%20in%20the%20vulnerable%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20dream%20of%20a%20miracle%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20high%20chances%20that%20in%20a%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20fought%20on%20hyper-religious%20nationalism%2C%20the%20very%20same%20Congress%20votes%20may%20shift%20to%20the%20BJP.%20The%20battle%20of%202024%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20not%20a%20mathematical%20calculation%20for%20the%20opposition%2C%20and%20surely%20cannot%20be%20won%20by%20diluting%20the%20secular%20agenda%20or%20becoming%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20political%20replica.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20BJP-RSS%20is%20fighting%20an%20ideological%20and%20political%20battle%20against%20the%20Indian%20Republic%2C%20of%20which%20electoral%20victories%20are%20one%20among%20the%20many%20strategies%2C%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20including%20the%20Congress%20and%20its%20supporters%2C%20cannot%20dream%20of%20saving%20the%20idea%20of%20India%20by%20staging%20an%20unprincipled%20electoral%20battle%20with%20the%20diluted%20versions%20of%20the%20same%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESerious%20politics%20demand%20imagination%20and%20preparation%20beyond%202024%20and%20the%20electoral%20arena%20with%20an%20agenda%20and%20vision%20for%20a%20battle%20for%20substantive%20equality%2C%20social-economic%20justice%20and%20fraternity%2C%20and%20not%20a%20diluted%20version%20of%20Hindutva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fshivasundar%5C%22%3EShivasundar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20activist%20and%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20based%20in%20Bangalore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703073623000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06200522%2FF80eu2gWkAATe66.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-take-on-bjp-mere-electoral-battle-not-enough%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Since%20the%20assembly%20election%20results%2C%20many%20have%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Congress%20has%20been%20intact%20despite%20its%20defeats.%20What%20they%20miss%20is%20the%20steep%20fall%20in%20the%20traditional%20Hindu%20vote%20base%20of%20the%20Congress%20is%20compensated%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20its%20Muslim%20vote%20share.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-take-on-bjp-mere-electoral-battle-not-enough%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ireland%20brings%20legal%20action%20against%20UK%20under%20European%20Convention%20on%20Human%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703073600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F70x70%2Fskynews-micheal-martin-ireland_6399232.jpg%3F20231220135908%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firish-government-launches-legal-challenge-against-uks-controversial-northern-ireland-legacy-bill-13034806%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Irish%20government%20is%20to%20bring%20a%20legal%20case%20against%20the%20UK%20under%