he%20ban.%20We%20will%20soon%20hold%20a%20massive%20protest%20in%20Gadag%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhubballi%2Fworries-mount-as-onion-prices-drop-after-centres-export-ban%2Farticleshow%2F106056450.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Salim%20Byhatti%2C%20president%20of%20the%20onion%2Fpotato%20merchants%20association%2C%20APMC%2C%20Hubballi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnion%20farmers%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhubballi%2Fworries-mount-as-onion-prices-drop-after-centres-export-ban%2Farticleshow%2F106056450.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eurged%20the%20government%20to%20announce%20a%20minimum%20support%20price%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20onions%20and%20lift%20the%20export%20ban%20to%20protect%20farmers%20from%20further%20losses.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703070033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12135301%2FOnions.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fonion-export-ban-worsens-farmer-distress-could-cost-india-its-overseas-market%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Questions%20have%20been%20raised%20on%20if%20India%20is%20losing%20an%20established%20international%20market%20for%20its%20onions%20as%20Nepal%20and%20others%20begin%20assessing%20alternatives%20to%20the%20Indian%20onion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fonion-export-ban-worsens-farmer-distress-could-cost-india-its-overseas-market%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Telecom%20Bill%202023%20Is%20a%20Repackaged%20Version%20of%20the%20Archaic%20Colonial%20Law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20154844%2Fsunset-5423633_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecommunications%20Bill%2C%202023%20(%E2%80%9CTelecom%20Bill%2C%202023%E2%80%9D)%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20December%2018%2C%20almost%20a%20year%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20consultation%20process%20for%20its%202022%20counterpart%2C%20i.e.%20the%20draft%20Indian%20Telecommunication%20Bill%2C%202022%20(%E2%80%9CTelecom%20Bill%2C%202022%E2%80%9D).%20After%20several%20reported%20inter-ministerial%20discussions%20over%20the%20year%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Telecommunications%20(%E2%80%9CDoT%E2%80%9D)%20has%20released%20a%20repackaged%20version%20of%20the%20colonial%201885%20law%20it%20meant%20to%20overhaul%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20retain%20the%20draconian%20surveillance%20and%20internet%20suspension%20powers%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20should%20you%20care%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaws%20governing%20telecommunication%20services%20in%20the%20country%20have%20historically%20been%20used%20and%20misused%20to%20surveil%20our%20devices%20and%20suspend%20our%20internet.%20With%20changing%20times%2C%20these%20laws%20are%20also%20evolving%2C%20expanding%20the%20scope%20of%20applicability%20to%20new%20and%20emerging%20services.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1tX5sTSZEgo-9b3fVoInXFlUY93ZlFcYj%2Fview%3Fref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3ETelecom%20Bill%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20attempted%20to%20include%20online%20communication%20services%20(Signal%2C%20Zoom%2C%20Skype%2C%20Gmail)%20under%20the%20licensing%20regime%20historically%20applicable%20to%20broadcasting%20services.%20The%20expansion%20of%20surveillance%20and%20suspension%20powers%20from%20traditional%20broadcasting%20services%20to%20online%20communication%20services%20will%20cause%20irreparable%20damage%20to%20user%20rights%20and%20democratic%20freedoms.%C2%A0%20Definitional%20ambiguity%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1U56m1jE8CsLH7GMl5DTOu3iA4TxOito8%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dsharing%5C%22%3ETelecom%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaves%20us%20worried%20and%20confused%20about%20its%20application%20to%20internet%20services.%20In%20any%20scenario%2C%20the%20bill%20will%20have%20implications%20for%20our%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%20as%20well%20as%20our%20constitutional%20freedoms%20such%20as%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20right%20to%20receive%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20journey%20of%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%20from%202022%20till%202023%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20was%20released%20for%20public%20consultation%20on%20September%2021%2C%202022%2C%C2%A0%20following%20the%20release%20of%20the%20consultation%20paper%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9CNeed%20for%20a%20new%20legal%20framework%20governing%20Telecommunication%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20which%20was%20published%20on%20July%2023%2C%202022.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20which%20was%20released%20merely%20three%20weeks%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20consultation%20period%20for%20the%20paper%2C%20inserted%20controversial%20provisions%2C%20which%20was%20not%20present%20in%20the%20latter.%20In%20a%20response%20to%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(%E2%80%9CRTI%E2%80%9D)%20filed%20by%20us%2C%20the%20DoT%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1cRUKSbOO0lzpy6ohWTKhBzCl-ezSG40H%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dshare_link%26ref%3Dstatic.internetfreedom.in%5C%22%3Eshared%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20responses%20it%20received%20on%20the%20consultation%20paper%20%5BRead%20our%20comments%20on%20the%20paper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.internetfreedom.in%2Fcomments-on-the-consultation-paper-on-the%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%5D.%20The%20DoT%20however%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fhttps-internetfreedom-in-digital-transparency-report-for-january-2023%2F%5C%22%3Erefused%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20share%20the%20comments%20it%20received%20on%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20which%20were%20invited%20till%20late%20last%20year%20%5BRead%20our%20comments%20on%20the%20paper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Four-response-to-the-draft-telecom-bill-2022%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%5D.%20The%20absence%20of%20such%20disclosures%20make%20the%20reasoning%2Finspiration%20behind%20the%20changes%20non-transparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERepackaged%20control%2C%20replicated%20language%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98statement%20of%20objects%20and%20reasons%E2%80%99%20under%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20acknowledges%20the%20need%20to%20create%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Clegal%20and%20regulatory%20framework%20that%20focuses%20on%20safe%20and%20secure%20telecommunication%20network%20that%20provides%20for%20digitally%20inclusive%20growth%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20the%20aim%20of%20introducing%20such%20a%20bill%20was%20to%20%E2%80%8B%E2%80%8Bcreate%20a%20modern%20and%20future-ready%20comprehensive%20framework%20for%20the%20telecommunication%20sector%20in%20India%20which%20is%20currently%20governed%20by%20several%20colonial%20laws.%20While%20we%20agree%20with%20the%20need%20to%20reform%20the%20laws%20governing%20the%20sector%2C%20we%20dispute%20the%20approach%20adopted%20by%20the%20DoT%20to%20do%20so.%20Key%20provisions%20relating%20to%20surveillance%20and%20internet%20suspension%2C%20which%20have%20a%20long%20lasting%2C%20profound%20impact%20on%20our%20digital%20rights%2C%20have%20been%20replicated%20verbatim%20from%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%20of%201885.%20It%20will%20be%20unfair%20to%20say%20that%20the%20bill%20has%20not%20undergone%20changes%20in%20phrasing%2C%20but%20it%20will%20also%20be%20unfair%20to%20equate%20this%20change%20with%20reform.%20A%20contested%20provision%20of%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20i.e.%20licensing%2C%20has%20been%20replaced%2C%20only%20in%20name%2C%20by%20a%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Cauthorisation%E2%80%9D.%20The%20fundamental%20function%20of%20issuing%20authorisation%20is%20still%20an%20exclusive%20right%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%20Reliance%20on%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20safety%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20grounds%20to%20empower%20the%20Union%20government%20with%20powers%20to%20temporarily%20possess%2C%20suspend%2C%20intercept%2C%20detain%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20or%20telecommunication%20network%20from%20an%20authorised%20entity%20is%20nothing%20more%20than%20an%20old%20trick%20of%20the%201885%20playbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmbiguity%20around%20fundamental%20concepts%20of%20scope%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20backlash%20received%20by%20the%20DoT%20during%20the%20public%20consultation%20on%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20was%20around%20the%20wide%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%20services%E2%80%99%20which%20explicitly%20included%20a%20long%20list%20of%20online%20communication%20services.%20The%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%E2%80%99%20%5BClause%202(p)%5D%20read%20with%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%20services%E2%80%99%20%5BClause%202(t)%5D%20is%20now%20heavily%20diluted%20and%20truncated%2C%20creating%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20scope%20of%20applicability%20to%20internet%20services.%20Without%20this%20clarity%2C%20it%20creates%20hindrances%20in%20foreseeing%20the%20impact%20on%20user%20rights%20and%20thus%20meaningfully%20responding%20to%20or%20analysing%20the%20bill.%20Such%20definitional%20ambiguity%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20intentional%2C%20leaves%20the%20scope%20wide%20enough%20for%20online%20communication%20services%20to%20be%20included%20within%20its%20ambit.%20If%20internet%20services%20are%20included%20in%20the%20law%E2%80%99s%20ambit%2C%20then%20the%20several%20alarming%20requirements%20related%20to%20surveillance%2C%20possession%2C%20suspension%2C%20authorisation%2C%20etc.%20will%20be%20applied%20to%20those%20services%20as%20well%2C%20deepening%20the%20threats%20to%20our%20rights%20and%20freedoms.%20To%20avoid%20expansion%20or%20re-interpretation%20of%20the%20scope%20in%20the%20future%2C%20the%20definition%20of%20telecommunication%20and%20telecommunication%20services%2C%20in%20the%20bill%20itself%2C%20must%20explicitly%20exclude%20internet%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThreats%20to%20user%20privacy%20and%20rights%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20deteriorates%20user%20rights%20in%20several%20other%20ways%2C%20many%20of%20which%20directly%20infringe%20on%20the%20user%E2%80%99s%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy.%20Clause%203(7)%20is%20one%20such%20privacy%20invading%20provision%20which%20imposes%20an%20obligation%20on%20any%20authorised%20entity%2C%20as%20notified%20by%20the%20Union%20govt%2C%20to%20identify%20the%20person%20to%20whom%20it%20provides%20telecom%20services%2C%20through%20use%20of%20any%20verifiable%20biometric%20based%20identification%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%20also%20contained%20a%20similar%20provision%20for%20licensed%20entities%2C%20but%20with%20safeguards%20and%20specificity.%20Section%204(3)(a)%20listed%20the%20various%20modes%20of%20authentication%20that%20may%20be%20used%20by%20the%20licensee%2C%20including%20offline%20authentication%2C%20and%20also%20explicitly%20mentioned%20alternatives%20authentication%20modes%20to%20Aadhaar%20such%20as%20passport.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cbiometric%E2%80%9D%20based%20identification%20mode%20did%20not%20even%20feature%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022.%20This%20inclusion%20of%20%E2%80%9Cverifiable%20biometric%20based%20identification%E2%80%9D%20raises%20fears%20that%20it%20may%20provide%20a%20legislative%20basis%20for%20the%20mandatory%20linking%20of%20Aadhaar%20to%20mobile%20phones%20which%20was%20ruled%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Faadhaar-verdict-supreme-court-judgment-uidai-5374829%2F%5C%22%3Eunconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Thus%2C%20this%20provision%20is%20bereft%20of%20safeguards%20on%20many%20levels%2C%20but%20is%20most%20prominently%20inadequate%20for%20pushing%20technology%20solutions%20for%20a%20country%20which%20is%20still%20largely%20not%20digital%20literate.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20informed%20understanding%20of%20how%20such%20biometric%20data%20will%20be%20used%2C%20stored%2C%20processed%2C%20and%20shared%20among%20majority%20of%20the%20public%2C%20and%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20non-robust%20data%20protection%20act%20which%20provides%20wise%20ranging%20exemptions%20to%20the%20government%2C%20such%20technology%20should%20not%20be%20adopted%20for%20a%20routine%20procedure%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20offline%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20potentially%20privacy%20infringing%20provision%20is%20Clause%2029%20of%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20imposes%20a%20duty%20on%20users%20to%20not%20furnish%20any%20false%20information%20while%20establishing%20their%20identity%20for%20availing%20%E2%80%98telecommunication%20services%E2%80%99.%20If%20applicable%20to%20internet%20services%2C%20the%20ambiguous%20phrasing%20of%20Clause%203(7)%20and%2029%20will%20have%20damaging%20consequences%20for%20a%20user%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20stay%20anonymous%20while%20communicating.%20This%20can%20have%20a%20deleterious%20impact%20on%20vulnerable%20individuals%20such%20as%20whistleblowers%20and%20journalists%2C%20who%20wish%20to%20keep%20their%20identity%20anonymous.%20Services%20such%20as%20Twitter%20and%20Instagram%2C%20which%20currently%20provide%20users%20with%20the%20option%20to%20communicate%20anonymously%2C%20will%20possibly%20have%20to%20take%20back%20this%20facility%20if%20they%20wish%20to%20operate%20in%20India.%20The%20application%20of%20this%20clause%20in%20the%20context%20of%20traditional%20telecommunication%20services%20can%20be%20viewed%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20rising%20cybercrime%20in%20the%20country.%20Notably%2C%20the%20associated%20penalty%20for%20failing%20to%20comply%20with%20these%20provisions%20are%2C%20i.e.%20up%20to%20INR%2025%2C000%20for%20the%20first%20offence%20and%20for%20the%20second%20or%20subsequent%20offences%2C%20up%20to%20INR%2050%2C000%20for%20every%20day%20till%20the%20contravention%20continues.%20The%20imposition%20of%20such%20hefty%20fines%20must%20be%20avoided%20for%20such%20clauses%20given%20the%20low%20digital%20literacy%20rates%20in%20the%20country%20as%20well%20as%20to%20avoid%20the%20misuse%20of%20the%20associated%20penalty%20by%20authorities%2C%20to%20coerce%20users%20into%20mandatorily%20using%20Aadhaar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Telecommunications%20Bill%20Lays%20the%20Ground%20for%20Totalitarian%20Control%20of%20the%20Internet%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Ftelecommunications-bill-lays-the-ground-for-totalitarian-control-of-the-internet%5C%22%3ETelecommunications%20Bill%20Lays%20the%20Ground%20for%20Totalitarian%20Control%20of%20the%20Internet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECentralised%20executive%20control%20and%20powers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20to%20suspend%2C%20curtail%2C%20or%20revoke%20the%20authorisation%20or%20assignment%20in%20case%20of%20breach%20of%20any%20of%20its%20terms%20and%20conditions%20rests%20with%20the%20Union%20government%20%5BClause%2032(2)%5D.%20A%20similar%20provision%20to%20revoke%20the%20licence%20exists%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%2C%20but%20it%20does%20not%20have%20any%20provisions%20for%20suspension%20of%20the%20licence.%20The%20entirety%20of%20Clause%2020%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20temporarily%20possess%2C%20suspend%2C%20intercept%2C%20detain%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20%5B20(1)(a)%5D%2C%20to%20intercept%2C%20detain%2C%20disclose%2C%20or%20suspend%20any%20message%20or%20class%20of%20messages%20%5B20(2)(a)%5D%2C%20to%20direct%20suspension%20of%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20or%20class%20of%20telecommunication%20%5B20(2)(b)%5D%2C%20or%20to%20notify%20encryption%20and%20data%20processing%20standards%20%5B19(f)%5D%2C%20cements%20the%20colonial%20powers%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20which%20upon%20misused%20and%20if%20extended%20to%20internet%20services%2C%20may%20become%20nothing%20less%20than%20draconian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClause%2022(3)%20read%20with%202(f)%20empowers%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20notify%20%E2%80%98critical%20telecommunication%20infrastructure%E2%80%99%20and%20issue%20measures%20related%20to%20the%20protection%20of%20such%20telecommunication%20networks%20and%20services.%20Protection%20measures%20listed%20include%20collection%2C%20analysis%2C%20and%20dissemination%20of%20traffic%20data%2C%20wherein%20%E2%80%98traffic%20data%E2%80%99%20is%20defined%20as%20any%20data%20generated%2C%20transmitted%2C%20received%20or%20stored%20in%20telecommunication%20networks%20including%20data%20relating%20to%20the%20type%2C%20routing%2C%20duration%20or%20time%20of%20a%20telecommunication.%20This%20special%20categorisation%20and%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20notify%20them%2C%20provide%20rules%20for%20their%20standards%2C%20and%20give%20them%20directions%20did%20not%20exist%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885.%20Thus%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20retaining%20several%20provisions%20that%20centralised%20power%20and%20control%20with%20the%20Executive%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20has%20created%20new%20ones%20that%20does%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClause%2043%20is%20reflective%20of%20this%20effort%20as%20it%20confers%20quasi-judicial%20powers%20to%20any%20officer%20authorised%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Esearch%20any%20building%2C%20vehicle%2C%20vessel%2C%20aircraft%20or%20place%20in%20which%20he%20has%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20any%20unauthorised%20telecommunication%20network%E2%80%A6.%20in%20respect%20of%20which%20an%20offence%20punishable%20under%20section%2042%20has%20been%20committed%2C%20is%20kept%20or%20concealed%20and%20take%20possession%20thereof.%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20Such%20search%20and%20seizure%20powers%20are%20accompanied%20with%20the%20power%20to%20summon%20information%2C%20documents%2C%20or%20records%20in%20possession%20or%20control%20of%20any%20authorised%20entity%20if%20it%20is%20believed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20be%20necessary%20for%20any%20pending%20or%20apprehended%20civil%20or%20criminal%20proceedings%20%5BClause%2044%5D.%20Such%20powers%2C%20non-existent%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%2C%20may%20be%20open%20to%20misuse%20due%20to%20its%20ambiguous%20phrasing%2C%20absence%20of%20clear%20parameters%20of%20information%20that%20may%20be%20revealed%2C%20and%20overbroad%20grounds%20for%20revealing%20information%20due%20to%20the%20use%20of%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Capprehended%E2%80%9D.%20This%20vagueness%20may%20lead%20to%20overbroad%20requests%20for%20disclosure%20which%20could%20result%20in%20the%20violation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20users%2C%20especially%20if%20it%20is%20applicable%20to%20internet%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMissed%20opportunity%20for%20surveillance%20and%20suspension%20reform%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20replication%20of%20language%20from%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%20%5BSection%205(2)%5D%20to%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20%5BClause%2020(2)(a)%5D%2C%20maintaining%20surveillance%20powers%20without%20any%20meaningful%20oversight%20or%20accountability%20processes.%20This%20centralises%20power%20in%20the%20Union%20and%20State%20Executive%20and%20is%20contrary%20to%20Supreme%20Court%20judgements%20and%20advances%20in%20surveillance%20regulations%20in%20comparative%2C%20common%20law%20jurisdictions%20(see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2013%2F12%2F18%2Fsurveillance-and-privacy-in-india-iv-analysing-the-landmark-pucl-judgment%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprivacylibrary.ccgnlud.org%2Fcase%2Fjustice-ks-puttaswamy-ors-vs-union-of-india-ors%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fsurveillance-reform-pdpb%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Through%20Clause%2020(2)(b)%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20cements%20the%20internet%20suspension%20power%20with%20the%20DoT%20without%20putting%20in%20place%20any%20of%20the%20procedural%20safeguards%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Cem%3EAnuradha%20Bhasin%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20(2020)%20%5B3%20SCC%20637%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Information%20Technology%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fconcerned-with-frequent-internet-suspensions-parliamentary-committee-recommends-an-overhaul%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20also%20misses%20an%20opportunity%20to%20fix%20the%20shortcomings%20of%20the%20Temporary%20Suspension%20of%20Telecom%20Services%20(Public%20Emergency%20or%20Public%20Safety)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdot.gov.in%2Fcirculars%2Ftemporary-suspension-telecom-services-public-emergency-or-public-safety-rules-2017%5C%22%3ERules%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202017.%20If%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20becomes%20applicable%20to%20online%20communication%20services%2C%20service%20providers%20such%20as%20Whatsapp%2C%20Signal%20etc.%2C%20which%20adopt%20the%20privacy%20protecting%20practice%20of%20End-to-End%20encryption%20(%E2%80%9CE2EE%E2%80%9D)%2C%20may%20also%20be%20required%20to%20intercept%2C%20detain%2C%20disclose%2C%20or%20suspend%20any%20message%2C%20wherein%20%E2%80%9Cmessage%E2%80%9D%20is%20defined%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eany%20sign%2C%20signal%2C%20writing%2C%20text%2C%20image%2C%20sound%2C%20video%2C%20data%20stream%2C%20intelligence%20or%20information%20sent%20through%20telecommunication%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20%5BClause%202(g)%5D.%20The%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20has%20failed%20to%20introduce%20improvements%20in%20the%20surveillance%20and%20internet%20shutdown%20architecture%20of%20the%20country%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20privacy%2C%20transparency%2C%20and%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsers%20in%20the%20eye%20of%20the%20storm%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20penalty%20imposed%20on%20users%20for%20using%20unauthorised%20telecommunication%20services%2C%20either%20knowingly%20or%20having%20reason%20to%20believe%20it%20to%20be%20unauthorised%2C%20has%20been%20increased%20from%20Rs%2050%20in%20the%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%201885%20and%20Rs%201%20lakh%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20to%20a%20hefty%2010%20Lakh%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20%5BThird%20Schedule%5D.%20The%20ground%20%E2%80%9Chaving%20reason%20to%20believe%20so%E2%80%9D%20may%20be%20misused%20and%20may%20put%20the%20user%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20as%20it%20appears%20to%20place%20the%20burden%20on%20them%20to%20prove%20lack%20of%20knowledge%20about%20the%20authorisation%20status%20of%20any%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETroubling%20patterns%20of%20delegated%20legislation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20several%20of%20the%20legislations%20and%20draft%20bills%20released%20in%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20suffers%20from%20excessive%20delegation%20by%20according%20the%20Union%20government%20overbroad%20rule-making%20powers%20without%20introducing%20adequate%20safeguards.%20While%20some%20instances%20of%20delegated%20legislation%20are%20justifiable%2C%20even%20necessary%2C%20at%20several%20instances%20out%20of%20the%20total%2046%20instances%2C%20specificity%20in%20the%20Bill%20is%20left%20to%20future%20rulemaking.%20Leaving%20relevant%20clarifications%20open%20to%20details%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cnotified%E2%80%9D%20in%20certain%20instances%20such%20as%20providing%20exemption%20from%20and%20terms%20and%20conditions%20for%20authorisation%2C%20specifying%20duration%2C%20and%20manner%20of%20interception%2C%20disclosure%2C%20and%20suspension%20of%20telecommunication%20services%2C%20etc.%20contribute%20to%20increased%20uncertainty%2C%20vagueness%2C%20and%20raise%20concerns%20around%20arbitrary%20rule-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20improvements%20do%20exist%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023.%20For%20instance%2C%20an%20attempt%20to%20dilute%20TRAI%E2%80%99s%20powers%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20governance%20of%20this%20sector%20introduced%20in%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20has%20been%20reviewed%20and%20improved%20on%20in%20the%202023%20bill.%20The%20controversial%20provision%20in%20the%202022%20version%20allowing%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20sender%20of%20a%20message%20using%20telecommunication%20services%20to%20be%20made%20available%20to%20the%20user%20receiving%20such%20message%2C%20in%20such%20form%20as%20may%20be%20prescribed%2C%20has%20been%20removed%20in%C2%A0%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%23KillTheBill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20like%20its%202022%20counterpart%2C%20has%20retained%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternetfreedom.in%2Fthe-draft-indian-telecommunication-bill%2F%5C%22%3Ecolonial%20roots%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20missed%20an%20opportune%20moment%20for%20bringing%20about%20reform.%20The%20DoT%20must%20thus%20publicly%20release%20the%20comments%20received%20by%20it%20during%20the%20consultation%20on%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202022%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20transparency%20and%20accountability%2C%20so%20the%20stakeholders%20can%20gain%20insight%20into%20the%20DoT%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20for%20holding%20on%20to%20provisions%20of%20an%20archaic%20law.%20Secondly%2C%20we%20urge%20the%20DoT%20to%20withdraw%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20a%20right-centric%20version%20that%20protects%20and%20promotes%20individual%20rights.%20This%20version%20must%20be%20accompanied%20with%20a%20white%20paper%2F%20explanatory%20note%20with%20justifications%20and%20reasoning%20for%20introducing%20any%20changes%20introduced%20in%20comparison%20with%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%20of%202022%20as%20well%20as%202023.%20The%20DoT%20must%20also%20hold%20another%20consultation%2C%20that%20is%20broad%2C%20multi-city%2C%20in-person%20stakeholder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20is%20slated%20for%20passage%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20today%2C%20i.e.%20December%2020.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20crucial%20voice%20of%20the%20suspended%20140%2B%20opposition%20Members%20of%20Parliament%20and%20in%20light%20of%20the%20current%20state%20of%20chaos%2C%20disarray%2C%20protest%2C%20and%20walk%20outs%20in%20the%20Parliament%2C%20the%20Telecom%20Bill%2C%202023%20must%20not%20be%20passed.%20We%20also%20recommend%20the%20Union%20Government%20to%20appoint%20a%20Law%20Commission%20and%2For%20an%20unbiased%2C%20independent%20Standing%20Committee%20or%20expert%20body%20to%20look%20into%20the%20kinds%20of%20reforms%20needed%20for%20the%20telecommunication%20sector.%20Finally%2C%20the%20clarification%20about%20online%20communication%20services%20being%20excluded%20from%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20bill%20must%20be%20explicitly%20and%20clearly%20added%20in%20the%20text%20of%20the%20bill%20itself%2C%20and%20not%20be%20inserted%20in%20subsequent%2C%20not%20enforceable%20FAQs%20(frequently%20asked%20questions)%20or%20clarified%20through%20verbal%20statements%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exchange4media.com%2Famp%2Fdigital-news%2Fott-excluded-from-telecom-services-purview-in-new-draft-of-telecom-bill-2023-131514.html%5C%22%3EUnion%20Minister%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20unnamed%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelecom.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolicy%2Fno-decision-yet-on-having-similar-rules-for-otts-and-telcos-official%2F106138191%5C%22%3Esenior%2