ssed%20the%20contentious%20scheme%20in%20his%20soon-to-be%20memoirs%2C%20titled%20%3Cem%3EFour%20Stars%20of%20Destiny%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fin-his-memoir-gen-naravane-sheds-light-on-how-agnipath-scheme-evolved%2F1890826%2F%5C%22%3Ereviewed%20by%20the%20news%20agency%20PTI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20General%20Naravane%2C%20who%20was%20the%20Army%20chief%20from%20December%2031%2C%202019%20to%20April%2030%2C%202022%2C%20said%20he%20%E2%80%9Csounded%20out%E2%80%9D%20a%20%E2%80%98Tour%20of%20Duty%E2%80%99%20scheme%20in%20early%202020%20to%20induct%20soldiers%20for%20short-term%20tenure.%20But%20months%20later%2C%20the%20PMO%E2%80%99s%20formulation%20had%20a%20much%20wider%20scope%20and%20included%20all%20three%20services%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20in%20the%20army%20were%20taken%20by%20surprise%20by%20this%20turn%20of%20events%2C%20but%20for%20the%20navy%20and%20air%20force%2C%20it%20came%20like%20a%20bolt%20from%20the%20blue%2C%E2%80%9D%20General%20Naravane%20wrote.%20He%20had%20to%20explain%20to%20the%20Navy%20and%20Air%20Force%20chiefs%20that%20his%20initial%20proposal%20was%20only%20regarding%20the%20Army%20and%20he%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%C2%A075%25%20of%20the%20personnel%20recruited%20would%20be%20retained%2C%20while%2025%25%20should%20be%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fdefence-ministry-announces-agnipath-scheme-for-soldier-recruitment%5C%22%3Eannounced%20the%20Agnipath%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20June%2014%2C%202022%2C%20it%20said%20only%2025%25%20of%20recruits%20would%20be%20retained%20while%20the%20rest%20would%20be%20released%20after%20the%20completion%20of%20their%20four-year%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20writes%20in%20the%20book%2C%C2%A0%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20had%20first%20sounded%20out%20the%20PM%20about%20the%20Tour%20of%20Duty%20scheme%2C%20it%20was%20more%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20a%20short-service%20option%20at%20the%20soldier%20level%2C%20similar%20to%20the%20Short%20Service%20Commission%20scheme%20for%20officers%20that%20was%20already%20in%20vogue%E2%80%A6.%20Just%20as%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20SSC%20officers%20are%20taken%20each%20year%2C%20likewise%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20jawans%20would%20be%20similarly%20enrolled%20and%20released%20after%20the%20completion%20of%20their%20%E2%80%98tour%E2%80%99%20with%20the%20option%20of%20re-enlisting%20for%20another%20tour%2C%20if%20found%20to%20be%20fit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20did%20not%20make%20much%20headway%20initially%20because%20of%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20and%20the%20clashes%20between%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20armies%20in%20Galwan%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20in%20mid-2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20office%20(PMO)%20was%20considering%20this%20proposal%20but%20with%20a%20much%20wider%20scope%20and%20applicability.%20In%20the%20PMO%20formulation%2C%20not%20only%20should%20the%20complete%20intake%20of%20the%20year%20be%20short-service%20based%2C%20but%20it%20would%20also%20apply%20to%20all%20three%20services%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%2C%20published%20by%20Penguin%20Random%20House%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20become%20a%20tri-service%20matter%2C%20it%20now%20fell%20on%20Chief%20of%20Defence%20Staff%20Gen%20Bipin%20Rawat%20to%20take%20the%20proposal%20forward%2C%20albeit%20with%20the%20Army%20remaining%20the%20lead%20service%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20PTI%2C%20General%20Naravane%20wrote%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20for%20a%20first-year%20Agniveer%20was%20initially%20an%20all-inclusive%20Rs%2020%2C000%20per%20month.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20just%20not%20acceptable.%20Here%2C%20we%20were%20talking%20about%20a%20trained%20soldier%20who%20was%20expected%20to%20lay%20down%20his%20life%20for%20the%20country.%20Surely%20a%20soldier%20could%20not%20be%20compared%20with%20a%20daily%20wage%20labourer%3F%20Based%20on%20our%20very%20strong%20recommendations%2C%20this%20was%20later%20raised%20to%20Rs%2030%2C000%20per%20month%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20writes%20in%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20clashes%20with%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fagnipath-scheme-surprised-army-it-was-a-bolt-out-of-the-blue-for-navy-and-air-force-former-army-chief-writes-in-forthcoming-memoir%2Farticle67655104.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20book%20also%20details%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbehind-the-scenes%20events%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20stand-off%20with%20China%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20in%20mid-2020%2C%20when%20clashes%20between%20the%20two%20armies%20led%20to%20the%20deaths%20of%2021%20Indian%20soldiers%20and%20at%20least%20four%20Chinese%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Naravane%20writes%20that%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20told%20him%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EJo%20ucchit%20samjho%20woh%20karo%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(do%20whatever%20you%20deem%20appropriate)%20on%20the%20night%20of%20August%2031%2C%20terming%20the%20situation%20as%20%E2%80%9Cnearing%20breaking%20point%E2%80%9D.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20both%20sides%20had%20moved%20tanks%20near%20Rechin%20La%20on%20the%20south%20bank%20of%20Pangong%20Tso%2C%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20in%20my%20den%20at%20Army%20House%2C%20with%20the%20map%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20Ladakh%20on%20one%20wall%2C%20Eastern%20Command%20on%20another.%20They%20were%20unmarked%20maps%2C%20but%20as%20I%20looked%20at%20them%2C%20I%20could%20visualise%20the%20location%20of%20each%20and%20every%20unit%20and%20formation.%20We%20were%20ready%20in%20all%20respects%2C%20but%20did%20I%20really%20want%20to%20start%20a%20war%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20country%20was%20in%20bad%20shape%2C%20reeling%20under%20the%20Covid%20pandemic.%20The%20economy%20was%20faltering%2C%20global%20supply%20chains%20had%20broken%20down.%20Would%20we%20be%20able%20to%20ensure%20a%20steady%20supply%20of%20spares%2C%20etc.%2C%20under%20these%20conditions%2C%20in%20case%20of%20a%20long-drawn-out%20action%3F%20%E2%80%A6%20Who%20were%20our%20supporters%20in%20the%20global%20arena%2C%20and%20what%20about%20the%20collusive%20threat%20from%20China%20and%20Pakistan%3F%20A%20hundred%20different%20thoughts%20flashed%20through%20my%20mind.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20moments%20of%20reflection%2C%20he%20called%20up%20the%20then%20Northern%20Army%20Commander%20Lt%20General%20Y.K.%20Joshi%20and%20told%20him%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20cannot%20be%20the%20first%20ones%20to%20fire%E2%80%9D%20because%20%E2%80%9Cit%20would%20provide%20the%20Chinese%20with%20an%20excuse%2C%20a%20casus%20belli%2C%20to%20escalate%20and%20paint%20us%20as%20the%20aggressors%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%2C%20I%20told%20him%20to%20move%20a%20troop%20of%20our%20tanks%20right%20to%20the%20forward%20slopes%20of%20the%20Pass%20and%20depress%20their%20guns%20so%20that%20the%20PLA%20would%20be%20staring%20down%20the%20barrels%20of%20our%20guns%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20writes.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20done%20forthwith%20and%20the%20PLA%20tanks%2C%20which%20had%20by%20then%20reached%20within%20a%20few%20hundred%20metres%20of%20the%20top%2C%20stopped%20in%20their%20tracks.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTheir%20light%20tanks%20would%20have%20been%20no%20match%20for%20our%20medium%20tanks.%20It%20was%20a%20game%20of%20bluff%20and%20the%20PLA%20blinked%20first%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20writes%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20PLA%20moved%20troops%20from%20Moldo%20to%20the%20area%20of%20Chuti%20Changla%20towards%20the%20south%20bank%20of%20Pangong%20Tso%20on%20the%20intervening%20night%20of%20August%2029-30.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20PLA%20reaction%20was%20not%20long%20in%20coming.%20On%20the%2030th%20evening%20itself%2C%20they%20moved%20forward%20some%20troops%20in%20the%20area%20of%20the%20Kailash%20Range%2C%20stopping%20about%20500%20metres%20short%20of%20our%20locations%20and%20started%20digging%20in.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20PLA%20locations%20were%20at%20lower%20heights%20and%20directly%20under%20Indian%20observation.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20such%2C%20they%20were%20of%20no%20threat%20to%20us%2C%20but%20if%20they%20were%20to%20come%20up%20in%20strength%20and%20try%20to%20outflank%20or%20surround%20our%20localities%2C%20then%20we%20would%20have%20to%20take%20action.%20The%20situation%20was%20tense%20and%20nearing%20breaking%20point.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703064575000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20141044%2Fnaravane.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fagnipath-scheme-bolt-out-of-the-blue-navy-air-force-former-army-chief-naravane-memoirs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20forthcoming%20memoirs%20titled%20'Four%20Stars%20of%20Destiny'%2C%20General%20Naravane%20says%20that%20he%20had%20initially%20proposed%20a%20four-year%20tour%20of%20duty%20scheme%20only%20for%20the%20Army.%20The%20PMO's%20formulation%20expanded%20it%20to%20all%20three%20services%2C%20he%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fagnipath-scheme-bolt-out-of-the-blue-navy-air-force-former-army-chief-naravane-memoirs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Detainees%20Sharing%20Cells%20With%20Criminals%E2%80%99%3A%20Human%20Rights%20Violations%20in%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20Detention%20Centres%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20131757%2Fimage-1646.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20completion%20of%20construction%20and%20the%20commencement%20of%20operations%20at%20India%E2%80%99s%20l%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1045195%2Finside-indias-largest-detention-centre-it-is-better-to-die-than-live-with-no-hope%5C%22%3Eargest%20detention%20centre%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Matia%20transit%20camp%20in%20Goalpara%20district%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20sparked%20a%20public%20outcry%20among%20the%20people%20of%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20risk%20of%20detention%20are%20individuals%20suspected%20to%20be%20illegal%20migrants%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20categorised%20as%20foreigners%2C%20doubtful%20voters%20and%20people%20excluded%20from%20the%20NRC%20(National%20Register%20of%20Citizens)%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20contentious%20issue%20of%20the%20citizenship%20crisis%20in%20Assam%2C%20detention%20centres%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.parichay.org.in%2Fblog-page%2Fa-fact-sheet-on-detention-centres-in-india%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20operational%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20state%20since%202010.%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20detention%20centres%20have%20consistently%20raised%20humanitarian%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20to%20liberty%2C%20a%20non-negotiable%20aspect%20of%20human%20rights%2C%20is%20impeded%20by%20detention%20and%20arbitrary%20arrest.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20sub-human%20and%20morally%20questionable%20treatment%20of%20the%20detainees%20within%20these%20clandestine%20facilities%2C%20strips%20them%20of%20their%20basic%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%E2%80%99%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20team%20conducted%20primary%20field%20interviews%20to%20unpack%20how%20these%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20explores%20how%20these%20detention%20centres%20act%20as%20%E2%80%98sites%20of%20exception%E2%80%99%20and%20push%20individuals%20towards%20rightlessness%2C%20leaving%20those%20labelled%20stateless%20with%20scant%20rights%20to%20shield%20from%20the%20questionable%20treatment.%20The%20name%20of%20the%20interviewee%20has%20been%20changed%20to%20maintain%20confidentiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaught%20in%20a%20legal%20void%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20her%20own%20experience%20of%20statelessness%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOrigins-Totalitarianism-Hannah-Arendt%2Fdp%2F0156701537%3Fots%3D1%26tag%3Dthneyo0f-20%26linkCode%3Dw50%5C%22%3EHannah%20Arendt%3C%2Fa%3E%20observed%20that%20the%20requirement%20for%20inclusion%20in%20a%20political%20community%20or%20nation-state%20is%20the%20predicament%20to%20guarantee%20even%20basic%20human%20rights.%20The%20denationalised%2C%20therefore%2C%20experience%20rightlessness%20as%20a%20result%20of%20statelessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20fissures%20of%20globalisation%20resulted%20in%20states%20drawing%20boundaries%2C%20pushing%20huge%20populations%20towards%20the%20periphery%20of%20statelessness%2C%20the%20detention%20centres%20have%20evolved%20as%20spaces%20where%20this%20form%20of%20rightlessness%20is%20worst%20experienced%2C%20with%20no%20guarantee%20about%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20life%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181208%2Fimage-1642.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22895%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181208%2Fimage-1642.png%20760w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181208%2Fimage-1642-300x211.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689890%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20classroom%20of%20Forest%20Learning%20Centre%20(FLC)%20at%20Laimuti%20village%2C%20Chirang%20District%2C%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.law.harvard.edu%2Filj%2F2023%2F06%2Ffinding-hope-for-the-hopeless-detention-statelessness-and-international-criminal-law%2F%23_ftnref14%5C%22%3ERefugee%20Convention%20of%201951%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20member%20states%20cannot%20detain%2C%20expel%2C%20or%20return%20immigrants%2C%20even%20if%20they%20have%20entered%20without%20permission.%20Given%20that%20India%20is%20not%20a%20member%20state%2C%20it%20is%20not%20bound%20by%20the%20rules%20placed%20by%20the%20Convention%2C%20and%20hence%2C%20it%20has%20been%20seen%20taking%20stringent%20actions%20against%20the%20illegal%20migrants%2C%20through%20detection%2C%20detention%2C%20and%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deplorable%20conditions%20faced%20by%20detainees%20came%20to%20the%20limelight%2C%20particularly%20after%20Harsh%20Mander%2C%20the%20special%20monitor%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%2C%20exposed%20the%20dire%20situation%20within%20the%20camps.%20The%20questionable%20treatment%20inflicted%20upon%20detainees%20is%20perhaps%20best%20exemplified%20by%20the%20case%20of%20Sumi%20Goswami.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumi%20Goswami%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20Matia%20detention%20centre%20on%20account%20of%20a%20technical%20error%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20Foreigners%20Tribunal.%20Despite%20possessing%20all%20the%20necessary%20documents%2C%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20live%20in%20the%20detention%20camp%20for%20three%20days%2C%20after%20which%20she%20was%20released%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20recounting%20her%20time%20at%20the%20detention%20centre%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNobody%20would%20understand%20what%20I%20have%20gone%20through.%20Only%20I%20can.%20If%20you%20have%20not%20been%20to%20a%20detention%20camp%2C%20you%20will%20not%20understand%20what%20it%20is%20to%20live%20there.%20Never%20did%20I%20think%20I%20would%20have%20to%20experience%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20living%20conditions%20there%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20about%2014%20to%2015%20people%20within%20one%20cell%2C%20with%20one%20attached%20bathroom.%20The%20first%20day%20I%20went%20there%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20to%20notice%20that%20the%20doors%20of%20the%20bathrooms%20are%20partially%20built%2C%20such%20that%20your%20face%20can%20be%20seen%20from%20outside.%20On%20asking%20an%20official%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20it%20was%20%5Bbuilt%20in%20that%20way%5D%20to%20restrict%20the%20inmates%20from%20committing%20suicides.%20The%20foul%20smell%20from%20the%20bathroom%2C%20because%20of%20the%20partially%20built%20doors%2C%20made%20it%20unbearable%20to%20live%20there%2C%20let%20alone%20eat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoswami%20further%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20could%20not%20sleep%20for%20two%20nights%20straight.%20I%20remained%20seated%20the%20whole%20time.%20Never%20in%20my%20life%20had%20I%20used%20the%20type%20of%20bed%20and%20mattress%20they%20provided%20me%20with.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181314%2Fimage-1643.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22941%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181314%2Fimage-1643.png%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F19181314%2Fimage-1643-300x195.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689891%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22611%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWeavers%20at%20the%20ant%20weaving%20centre%20at%20Rowmari%2C%20Chirang%20District%2C%20Assam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcjp.org.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F11%2FNHRC-Report-Assam-Detention-Centres-26-3-2018-1.pdf%5C%22%3EUNHRC%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20state%20prisons%20should%20not%20be%20used%20for%20detention%2C%20the%20centres%20of%20Assam%20are%20sub-parts%20of%20normal%20jails%2C%20and%20hence%2C%20the%20declared%20%E2%80%9Cforeigners%E2%80%9D%20are%20often%20placed%20within%20the%20same%20cells%20with%20the%20convicted%20prisoners.%20Sumi%20Goswami%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20asked%20one%20of%20the%20inmates%20what%20she%20was%20doing%20there%20and%20she%20said%20she%20murdered%20her%20brother%20for%20land.%20I%20asked%20another%20woman%20the%20same%20question%20and%20she%20said%20she%20was%20arrested%20for%20smuggling%20drugs.%20How%20can%20you%20sleep%20peacefully%20in%20a%20room%20with%20criminals%20around%20you%3F%20Someone%20might%20come%20and%20kill%20you%2C%20you%20never%20know.%20Why%20are%20the%20D-voters%20kept%20with%20these%20criminals%3F%20What%20crime%20did%20they%20commit%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumi%20sighed%20as%20she%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20one%20of%20the%20inmates%20told%20me%20that%20she%20was%20living%20there%20for%20ten%20years%2C%20I%20was%20shocked.%20I%20would%20not%20be%20alive%20if%20I%20had%20to%20live%20there%20forever.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20all%20detainees%20are%20compelled%20to%20live%20in%20substandard%20conditions%2C%20women%20experience%20even%20worse%20conditions%2C%20including%20complaints%20of%20sexual%20abuse%20and%20forced%20abortions%2C%20among%20other%20forms%20of%20violence.%20The%20differential%20experiences%20of%20women%20in%20detention%20will%20be%20dealt%20with%20in%20the%20next%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20comprehensive%20legal%20framework%20must%20be%20established%2C%20ensuring%20the%20fair%20and%20humane%20treatment%20of%20detainees%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20immigration%20status.%20Resolving%20legal%20ambiguities%2C%20providing%20an%20adequate%20legal%20defence%2C%20and%20addressing%20the%20specific%20vulnerabilities%20of%20detainees%20are%20essential%20steps%20to%20bring%20detention%20practices%20in%20Assam%20in%20line%20with%20international%20human%20rights%20standards.%20The%20urgency%20of%20this%20task%20is%20underscored%20by%20the%20profound%20impact%20on%20the%20lives%20and%20well-being%20of%20those%20affected%20by%20the%20current%20state%20of%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAll%20photographs%20have%20been%20taken%20by%20CNES%20researchers%20during%20field%20work%20in%20Assam.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20Samragnee%20Chakraborty%20and%20Hima%20Trisha%20M.%20are%20Senior%20Research%20Analysts%20(CNES).%20Yashovardhan%20Chaturvedi%2C%20Nitya%20Arora%2C%20Rieshav%20Chakraborty%20and%20Aman%20Chain%20are%20Research%20Assistants%20with%20CNES.%20The%20authors%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Dr.%20Salah%20Punathil%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad%20for%20his%20guidance%20and%20support.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20by%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20explores%20the%20detention%20centres%20in%20Assam%20as%20spaces%20violating%20human%20rights%20and%20disproportionately%20affecting%20migrants.%20These%20are%20penned%20down%20from%20the%20documented%20findings%20of%20a%20recent%20Azaad%20Awaaz%20edition.%20Click%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazaadawaazcnes.wordpress.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20access%20the%20work%20of%20Azaad%20Awaaz%2C%20an%20initiative%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20working%20on%20issues%20of%20social%20exclusion%2C%20marginalization%2C%20and%20discrimination%20experienced%20by%20vulnerable%2C%20precarious%20communities%20across%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703062822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20131757%2Fimage-1646.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdetainees-sharing-cells-with-criminals-human-rights-violations-in-assams-detention-centres%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sumi%20Goswami%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20Matia%20detention%20centre%20on%20account%20of%20a%20technical%20error%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20Foreigners%20Tribunal.%20Her%20three-day%20experience%20at%20the%20centre%20exposes%20the%20inhumane%20treatment%20of%20detainees%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20immigration%20status.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdetainees-sharing-cells-with-criminals-human-rights-violations-in-assams-detention-centres%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22British%20businessman%20rescued%20by%20police%20after%20kidnapping%20in%20Ecuador%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703061960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-colin-armstrong-kidnapped_6398905.jpg%3F20231220083833%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fcolin-armstrong-police-in-ecuador-rescue-british-businessman-after-ranch-kidnap-13034695%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20British%20businessman%20who%20was%20kidnapped%20from%20his%20home%20in%20Ecuador%20has%20been%20rescued%20by%20police.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A99%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fcolin-armstrong-police-in-ecuador-rescue-british-businessman-after-ranch-kidnap-13034695%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Neighbourhood%20evacuated%20as%20hundreds%20of%20firefighters%20battle%20Cape%20Town%20wildfire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703060820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22h